  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the psychological and physical well being of older Syrian women and men refugees in Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving psychological well being of 1120 older Syrian women and men refugees in Lebanon by providing targeted Pyscho-social support activities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Older women and men, refugees</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Renovating two of Amel&apos;s centres to make them more older-people friendly including constructing wheelchair ramps | Training 15 centre staff and 20 volunteers to deliver psycho-social support and run activities specifically aimed at Ops | Running psychosocial support activities for 800 OPs at the centres, including: counselling, cultural activities to encouarge social interaction, physical exercise to help treat depression, anxiety and mitigate the impact of falls (a major cause of physical dependency and social isolation in OPs) | A GP will be available in the centres once a week to provide health checks and follow-ups to the approx 320 OPs with chronic conditions | Providing medical equipment for GPs to use such as scales, blood pressure manometres and measuring tapes.</narrative>
  </description>
